  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In patients with sepsis and AKI, increasing the intensity of renal replacement therapy from
      50 mL/kg/h (HVHF) to 85 mL/kg/h (EHVHF)will increase the survival at 28 days and 90 days.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
